div.p: SELANG, an island in the Eastern Seas, of inconsiderable size, flat and low. It lies off the southern coast of the island of Batchian, one of the Moluccas. The straits which it forms with this island are narrow, and not five feet in depth. The island forms two harbours with the mainland. Long. 124. 10. E. Lat. 0. 50. S.
